raw akas.title: Der Hundetrainer - Lucky Dogs mit Brandon McMillan

akas: Der Hundetrainer - Lucky Dogs mit Brandon McMillan Germany
akas from release info: Der Hundetrainer - Lucky Dogs mit Brandon McMillan Germany

1.title: Ginger
1.plot: A young Terrier mix might be the best friend a nine-year-old boy has been hoping for. But Brandon is in for a lot of work if he's going to transform this untrained dog into a well-mannered family member that's good with power tools, hover-boards, and cats.

2.title: Simba
2.plot: Before a young, energetic Golden Retriever can be a companion for a family, Brandon will have to teach him control and how to safely navigate around wheelchairs.

3.title: Zeus
3.plot: After surviving what could have only been canine distemper, a four-year Spaniel mix gets a second chance at Lucky Dog Ranch. But will the physical and neurological effects of the disease affect Zeus' ability to learn the common commands and find a forever home?

4.title: Betsy
4.plot: To prepare a young Foxhound for a woman hoping for a companion, Brandon will have to help the dog overcome her separation anxiety and keep her nose out of trouble.

5.title: Magnolia
5.plot: To prepare a Newfoundland mix for a schoolteacher hoping to bring her new dog to school with her, Brandon will have to make sure the dog has the control to be around children and distractions.

6.title: Fiona
6.plot: A family reaches out to Brandon in hopes of finding a companion for their current dog. Brandon thinks he may have a good match. But before the adoption is sealed, he'll have to make sure that Fiona is tested with kids and the family's dog.

7.title: Maddie
7.plot: Brandon rescues a malnourished Poodle mix, suffering from an upper respiratory infection, in hopes that she might be the perfect companion for a woman coming to grips with her own failing eyesight.

8.title: Henry
8.plot: Scarred by a previous dog attack, a married couple closes the door on future pet adoptions. But, if Brandon can teach a 2-year-old mini-poodle mix, named Henry, how to ring the bell to their hearts, they could open up their home to a new furry friend.

9.title: Dean
9.plot: To prepare a sweet poodle mix for a woman who has had six knee surgeries, Brandon must make sure that the dog has a perfect heel and can jump in and out of cars by himself.

10.title: Rainey
10.plot: Brandon rescues a gentle, yet consistently overlooked Staffordshire Bull Terrier in hopes of placing her in a home with another dog that is struggling with timidity.

11.title: Geo
11.plot: After rescuing, and gaining the trust, of a terrier mix that came from an abusive and neglectful situation, Brandon works hard to prepare the dog for life with a ride-share driver who wants a canine co-pilot to join her on the road.

12.title: A Higher Purpose
12.plot: Brandon checks in with former students and their adopters to find out how the dogs have been fulfilling a higher purpose as service animals.

13.title: Sammy
13.plot: After rescuing a senior dog that was abandoned by his previous family, Brandon introduces the troubled terrier to a new recreational activity that could keep the dog healthy, while helping him bond with two young victims of bullying.

14.title: Chester
14.plot: An abandoned poodle mix could be the perfect match for a lonely woman who is starting life over again. But before Brandon can connect this downcast duo, he must bring the cautious canine out of his shell.

15.title: Meaningful Matches
15.plot: Brandon rescues five different shelter dogs and trains them for their new forever families. In the end, these people and pet pairings prove to be truly meaningful matches for everyone involved.

1.title: Willie
1.plot: Animal trainer Brandon McMillan rescues untrained dogs from animal shelters and teaches them to be great pets. In the opener, Brandon works with a Tibetan terrier.

2.title: Vinnie
2.plot: Brandon helps a scared stray dog overcome its fears and learn what it's like to be loved by a California family.

3.title: Emmitt
3.plot: Brandon helps place a mixed breed dog named Emmit with a Los Angeles family, but the road to adoption is tricky.

4.title: Lolita
4.plot: A single dad and his three young boys adopt Lolita, a smart, sweet Chihuahua, who helps bring new life to the household. When Brandon learns Lolita's bad habit of dashing out the front door, he teaches her about boundaries.

5.title: Daisy
5.plot: A family hope to adopt Daisy, a terrier-poodle mix. The mom hopes that the dog will teach her daughter the responsibilities of having a pet. However, Daisy has a barking problem that Brandon must resolve to get her ready for her new home.

6.title: Luke
6.plot: Brandon rescues a shy German shepherd-Labrador mix and trains the dog to be a companion for a teacher and her students.

7.title: Randy
7.plot: Brandon finds a mixed poodle for a boy.

8.title: Oliver
8.plot: A homeless, severely underweight terrier mix is given a home with a Los Angeles family.

9.title: For Every Problem, There's a Solution
9.plot: Brandon works with a skittish dog that is frightened of its own shadow and with a cantankerous canine that barks incessantly.

10.title: Roxie
10.plot: A family selects a rescue dog that Brandon trains.

11.title: Coco
11.plot: Brandon rescues a border collie mix that is fearful of everyone.

12.title: Kai
12.plot: Kai is a dog who was found on the streets in Los Angeles and who was born blind on his left side. Brandon matches Kai to a woman who wants to take him to her grandmother's assisted living facility as a loving and calm therapy dog.

13.title: Hershey
13.plot: A dachshund mix is rescued and adopted by a family, but they worry that the small dog will have difficulty climbing the stairs in their two-story home.

14.title: Out of the Box
14.plot: Some of Brandon's most creative and surprising training moments are featured.

15.title: Flash
15.plot: A 6-month-old Chihuahua is rescued and taught the art of running alongside a bike.

16.title: Charlie
16.plot: A family look for a playmate for their lab, and Brandon suggests Charlie, an energetic black lab mix.

17.title: Jingles
17.plot: A pointer mix suffering from a bad case of kennel stress learns to shed anxiety and become an off-leash pet for an outdoor-loving family. Meanwhile, the family's daughter tries to overcome her personal fear of dogs.

18.title: A Family Affair!
18.plot: Brandon revisits some of his best family-inspired training moments.

19.title: Lucky
19.plot: A family adopt Lucky, a King Charles spaniel mix, and Lucky's training plunges into new depths when Brandon discovers the family have a pool in their backyard.

20.title: Barnaby
20.plot: Brandon rescues a tiny terrier named Barnaby.

21.title: Bailey
21.plot: Brandon rescues a 5-month-old pure-bred golden retriever.

22.title: Evan
22.plot: A family consider adopting a 4-year-old black Labrador mix.

23.title: Popcorn
23.plot: Brandon rescues Popcorn, a loveable English Bulldog saddled with a history of neglect. He's found a nurturing new owner in Simone, but can this out of shape bulldog keep up with her active lifestyle?

24.title: Jasmine
24.plot: Jasmine, the short haired pointer, was surrendered because of a tragic injury that takes thousands of dollars to fix. Can Brandon get Jasmine the care she needs and then find her the perfect home?

25.title: Best Of: Ultimate Tests
25.plot: From climbing a mountain to resisting temptation to swimming for safety, every dog that Brandon rescues has a unique set of challenges. And success will mean that they are ready for their new families.

26.title: Sadie
26.plot: Brandon faces one of his biggest challenges yet. He must find the perfect shelter dog to assist a woman with very special needs. And he'll have to devise a new form of training in order to make the match successful.

1.title: Cleo
1.plot: A Schnauzer mix's training takes an off-road detour when Brandon discovers her new family members are avid campers. To prove she's ready for the great outdoors, Cleo must earn her proficiency badge in camping etiquette.

2.title: Chance
2.plot: From red collar to white collar. Marketing Executive Christina wants to adopt a puppy she can take to her office. But if Chance, the Pointer Mix, wants to join the work force, he'll need to learn "get to work" on potty training.

3.title: Cora
3.plot: Cora, an eight-year-old Doberman mix, gets a new shot at life when potential owner, Nikki, decides to adopt a senior dog. But will Cora be able to shed a lifetime of bad habits to make way for a new talent?

4.title: Shadow
4.plot: A game of trust. Living alone for the first time in fifty years, retiree Gary seeks out a new companion in Shadow, a one-year old Chihuahua mix. But before they can make new memories together, Shadow must learn to put aside the trust issues of his past.

5.title: Pluto
5.plot: We're blasting off! Brandon rescues Pluto, a Tibetan terrier mix with gravity defying energy. But will Pluto's marking habit ground the adoption process before it can launch?

6.title: Best of: Overcoming Obstacles
6.plot: Age. Experience. Physical limitation. Every dog faces its own unique hurdles in training. But with Brandon's guidance, they're all capable of achieving new heights.

7.title: Sandy
7.plot: A golden retriever answers the call of duty for a wounded warrior who's in need. But to earn his service dog badge, Sandy must successfully complete Brandon's boot camp.

8.title: Biscuit
8.plot: A debilitating skin condition leaves a French bulldog mix with little hope for adoption, until an eleventh hour save gives him another shot at life. But will the family pool sink Biscuit's chance at a forever home?

9.title: Rosie
9.plot: Brandon helps turn a ten-month-old poodle mix into a therapy dog for a cancer survivor who's hoping to pay it forward. But, can managing one of life's most difficult challenges prepare Lori for the job of handling Rosie?

10.title: Wilson
10.plot: Lights, camera, action! An LA-based photographer sets his sights on finding the perfect mascot for his photography business. But if Wilson, the two-year old Lhasa Apso mix, wants to book the job, he'll need to channel his inner supermodel.

11.title: Brando
11.plot: Brando, the nine-month-old Rottweiler mix, gets a job offer he can't refuse. But preparing this eighty-pound puppy for office life could spell disaster.

12.title: Best Of: Transformations
12.plot: From makeovers to mindsets -every Lucky Dog goes through its own unique metamorphosis. Today we look back at some of this season's most dramatic, and heartwarming, "transformations."

13.title: Toto
13.plot: There's no place like home! A West Highland terrier mix catches the eye of a loving family looking to adopt their first dog. But will Toto's severe reaction to leashes jeopardize his storybook ending?

14.title: Grover
14.plot: Diamond in the Ruff! Grover, the two-year-old Poodle mix, might just be the perfect gem for an antique jewelry dealer looking for a new companion. But his deep-seated abandonment issues threaten to smudge his chance at a forever home.

15.title: Junior
15.plot: Dance Fever! After the sudden passing of his former companion, a retired vet hopes a six-month old Chihuahua mix will mend his broken heart. But when Junior's lack of motivation proves problematic, Brandon relies on his "bag of tricks" for inspiration.

16.title: Poppi
16.plot: After months of scouring shelters, Brandon thinks he's finally ready to cook up the perfect adoption for his Aunt Patti. But will Aunt Patti's epicurean lifestyle prove too much for this Cocker Spaniel's insatiable appetite?

17.title: Groot
17.plot: Follow the leader! When a submissive Dachshund mix proves difficult to train, Brandon seeks out additional assistance-and finds it in the paws of another trainer.

18.title: Stark
18.plot: Hoping to incorporate a new dog into their upcoming nuptials, Niki and Vien set their sights on a one-year-old Lhasa Apso mix named Stark. But before Stark can say "I do" to his new life, he'll need to stop objecting to his training.

19.title: Best of: One Step at a Time
19.plot: Every dog has its day... but training them takes a lot longer. Whether it's busting bad habits or cultivating news skills, true results require patience, consistency and above all else, taking it "one step at a time".

20.title: Sawyer
20.plot: A love for Retrievers comes full circle when one mother, whose life was saved by her childhood companion, seeks to adopt a dog for her own children. But if Sawyer, an eight-month old Labrador Retriever, wants to keep up with the family's active lifestyle, he'll need to add bike training to his resume.

21.title: Lily
21.plot: An impassioned mother seeks out Brandon's assistance in hopes of finding a service dog for her disabled daughter. But before Lily the two-year old Golden Retriever can join this new partnership, she'll need to prove that she's ready to shoulder the responsibility.

22.title: Kobe
22.plot: Game on! Brandon rescues an "untrainable" terrier mix that was abandoned by his original owner. But if Kobe wants a second chance at a stable home, he'll need to embrace the fundamentals of obedience and keep his head in the game.

23.title: Tweety
23.plot: A pint-sized Maltese mix could be the perfect remedy for one family's heartache. But before Tweety can take a new family under her wing, she'll need to focus on her own healing.

24.title: Leah
24.plot: Teacher's Pet. A special education teacher hopes to adopt a Golden Corgi mix for his family. But before Leah can go to her new home, she'll need to excel in and out of the classroom.

25.title: Shelby
25.plot: Shelby, the German Shepherd, doesn't just need a home, she needs a purpose. But will her disregard for personal space, trip up her chance at adoption?

26.title: Best of: Pairing Up
26.plot: Dogs are social animals that crave connection. But while some bonds come quickly, others take a little effort. So embrace the pack mentality, because today we're "pairing up".

1.title: Motu
1.plot: A cancer survivor with a passion for the ocean finds a kindred spirit in Motu, a spunky Maltese mix facing his own physical challenge. But before Motu can sail off into the sunset with Julie, he'll need to hone his kayaking skills with Brandon.

2.title: Bandit
2.plot: Brandon hopes to place an intelligent Border Collie mix named Bandit into the home of the Bisaccia family. But the adoption falls into jeopardy when mom, Erika, reveals her own personal battle with dog allergies.

3.title: Hazel
3.plot: Step up! A couple reaches out to Brandon in hopes of finding the perfect companion for their current dog. But before Hazel, a friendly terrier mix, can step into her new role, she'll need to conquer her own fear of stairs.

4.title: Glory
4.plot: After the tragic loss of her husband, a grandmother reaches out to Brandon in hopes of finding a furry new companion. But before Glory, an overweight Poodle mix, can join the family, she'll need to shape up with the help of Brandon's boot camp.

5.title: Murphy
5.plot: All work and no play! When a mischievous ten-month-old lab mix proves difficult to train, Brandon turns to toys to get results.

6.title: Kyrie
6.plot: To Serve and Protect. Brandon trains up a German Shepherd for a disabled veteran suffering from PTSD. But before Kyrie earns her service dog certification, she'll need to "pick up" the retrieve command.

7.title: Skye
7.plot: A game of trust. With Brandon's help, a skittish White Shepherd mix learns to embrace the world around her. But before Skye settles into her forever home, she'll need to forge an unlikely friendship with her new owner's horse.

8.title: Jemma
8.plot: An outgoing German Shepherd/Lab mix named Jemma could be the perfect canine ambassador for one woman's bed and breakfast. But before this seven-month-old puppy can assume her new role, she'll need to check her immaturity at the door.

9.title: Best Of: New Skills
9.plot: For five lucky shelter dogs, a forever home is right around the corner. But before they can step into their new lives, they'll all need to embrace "new skills".

10.title: Darby
10.plot: A middle school teacher reaches out to Brandon in hopes of adopting her very first dog. But if nine-month-old Darby wants to be the teacher's pet, she'll need to ace the common commands and prove she's ready for a classroom environment.

11.title: Lola
11.plot: When conventional training methods fail to pull a timid Welsh terrier mix named Lola out of her shell, Brandon recruits another "Lucky Dog in Training" to build Lola's confidence.

12.title: Riley
12.plot: Brandon transforms an "untrainable" two-year-old spaniel mix into one of the most talented agility dogs in Lucky Dog history. But will Riley's high-octane energy level prove too much for his potential mom, who suffers from chronic fatigue syndrome.

13.title: Maggie
13.plot: A spaniel mix named Maggie could be the perfect companion for a couple that recently lost their beloved golden retriever. But when Maggie's crippling fear of abandonment fails to respond to training, Brandon must turn to an outside source for help.

14.title: Best Of: Friendships
14.plot: They're called "Man's Best Friend", but for these five dogs, companionship defies age, size, gender and even species. Today we look back at some of this year's most heartwarming, and surprising, "friendships".

15.title: JoJo and Rhi Rhi
15.plot: Seeing Double! Unwilling to separate two lifelong pals, Brandon rescues JoJo and Rhi Rhi in hopes of placing them in the same forever home. But preparing them for Josh and Jonathon's jet-setting lifestyle means a lesson in flying the friendly skies and helming a stand-up paddleboard.

16.title: Maverick
16.plot: A devoted mother reaches out to Brandon in hopes of finding a support animal for her autistic son. But before one-year- old Maverick can officially become Dustin's wingman, he'll need to prove he has the temperament and social skills needed for his new role.

17.title: Odie
17.plot: A standard poodle named Odie could be the emotional support animal one young woman needs to conquer her severe anxiety. But before Odie can inspire Casey to go back to school, he'll first need to focus on his own graduation.

18.title: Hachi
18.plot: A homeless dog discovers a second chance with a once-homeless family that also spent time in and out of shelters. But before Hachi can become an official member of their public speaking crew, he'll need to transform his jumping habit into a new skill.

19.title: Scarlett
19.plot: Brandon rescues a two-year- old golden retriever that lives life in the fast lane. But when Scarlett's new family expresses an interest in taking her on road trips, she and Brandon must hit the road for a lesson in car etiquette.

20.title: Best Of: Handing Over the Reins
20.plot: Brandon prepares six shelter dogs for life after the ranch. But before he "hands over the reins" to their new families, he'll need to ensure that each new owner is ready for the responsibility and challenge of their new pup.

21.title: Stewie
21.plot: Brandon adopts a hand shy dachshund mix with a history of prior abuse. But before Stewie can officially settle into his loving new home, he'll need to prove that he can get along with his new brother, an eleven-year- old lab mix named Drogo.

22.title: Dodger
22.plot: Brandon rescues a calm schnauzer mix in hopes of placing him in a home with two autistic boys. But before Dodger gets called up to his new family, this underdog will need to prove that he's a team player.

23.title: Dottie
23.plot: A last minute rescue gives one senior dog the chance to live out her golden years in an exciting new role. But before Dottie can officially join Kris and his company's mascot Lucky, she'll need to embrace office etiquette and a love for travel.

24.title: Otto
24.plot: When a ranch employee takes a leave of absence to recover from an ongoing medical condition, Brandon trains an Australian cattle dog named Otto to be her companion... and her lifesaver.

25.title: Best Of: Special Connections
25.plot: Being pack animals, dogs possess an instinctual need to bond...but some bonds run deeper than others. To honor "man's best friend", we look back at some of this season's most heartwarming and inspirational connections.

26.title: Atlas
26.plot: Let freedom ring! Brandon thinks a black German shepherd has what it takes to become a service dog. But is one-year- old Atlas ready to shoulder the needs of a disabled veteran?

1.title: Charlotte
1.plot: When a heeler/Chihuahua mix loses her front leg due to neglect, Brandon steps in to give her a second chance. But preparing this special needs dog for a new life means teaching her to embrace her new body and finding her an equally "special" new home.

2.title: Spirit
2.plot: A street smart stray could strike the right chord with a rock n' roll family. But even if Brandon takes Spirit off the street, can he take the street out of Spirit?

3.title: Patches
3.plot: A timid Chihuahua/Min Pin mix presents Brandon with an unexpected obstacle as he works to train her to become an emotional support dog.

4.title: Ollie
4.plot: A middle-aged underdog gets a second chance with an empty-nester looking to spread her own wings. But will a history of neglect keep Ollie from embracing his adventurous new life?

5.title: Teri
5.plot: A retired couple reaches out to Brandon in hopes of finding a dog that will help them stay active in their daily fight against Parkinson's disease. But keeping this terrier's high-flying energy under control means channeling Teri's natural instincts into agility.

6.title: Olive
6.plot: Brandon trains a four-year-old poodle mix to work alongside a child advocate in the Missouri court system. But until Olive can prove she has the right temperament for the job, the jury remains out on her adoption.

7.title: Buddy
7.plot: A newlywed couple decides to jump-start their new life together by rescuing a puppy. But before Brandon says "I do" to this adoption, he'll need to get Buddy's unacceptable puppy habits under control.

8.title: Luna
8.plot: Brandon rescues a fun-loving German Shepherd that was found as a stray, but the dog's boundless energy threatens to be a deal breaker for a woman who was injured while walking a Shepherd in the past.

9.title: Sheela
9.plot: An Australian cattle dog mix seems like the perfect companion for an adventurous couple looking to embrace their retirement, but Brandon will need to work overtime to get Sheela's energy level under control.

10.title: Pax
10.plot: A young couple reaches out to Brandon in hopes of finding a playmate for their current dog. But before Pax can officially move in, she'll need to trade in her street habits for home etiquette.

11.title: Best Of: Home Improvement
11.plot: Even during some major construction at the Lucky Dog Ranch, Charlotte, Spirit, and three other dogs undergo life-changing renovations of their own.

12.title: Bear
12.plot: Big dogs often present unique training challenges, but the difficulty is compounded for Brandon when he is tasked with matching a high-energy Great Dane with a small-statured adopter.

13.title: Cosmo
13.plot: While a new family transforms their home to welcome a Yorkie mix, Brandon discovers a dark truth about the dog's past that changes the course of its training.

14.title: Lolly
14.plot: A Maltese mix appears to be an ideal lapdog for a senior, but the dog's boundless energy makes preparation for retirement living a lot of work for Brandon.

15.title: Bean
15.plot: When a Spaniel mix poses a unique opportunity for a high school student to develop her talents, Brandon realizes that won't happen if he can't get the dog under control.

16.title: Two's Company
16.plot: Discover how some of Brandon's rescued pups find additional purpose and extra challenges when they are paired with other dogs.

17.title: Dakota
17.plot: Before a rescued Malamute mix can provide comfort to a teenager with anxiety, Brandon must first help the dog overcome his own emotional issues.

18.title: Aussie
18.plot: Before he can find a new home for a Golden Retriever-Collie mix that was surrendered by his previous family, Brandon must help the dog overcome separation anxiety.

19.title: Foxy
19.plot: A Tennessee brindle mix gets an opportunity to help a young girl struggling with anxiety.

20.title: Arts & Entertainment
20.plot: Becoming a photographic model requires special training for a spaniel mix named Bean. The same is true for preparing Buddy, Lolly, Sheela and Dakota for their new lives in the world of arts and entertainment.

21.title: Sebastian
21.plot: In order to prepare a young Husky for life with his new family, Brandon must make sure that this former escape artist can part ways with his bad habits to prevent additional repeat visits to the local shelter.

22.title: Nikki
22.plot: Brandon tries to earn the trust of a Wheaten Terrier mix who shows difficulty adjusting to life outside of a cage in order to prepare it for a life in the busy tourist town of Solvang, Cal.

23.title: Evie
23.plot: Brandon teaches balance and water safety to Evie, a Chihuahua mix, so she can fit right in with a water-loving family.

24.title: Frankie
24.plot: Brandon works with Frankie, a beagle mix who's shy because of an abusive past.

25.title: Best Of: Where Are They Now?
25.plot: When Brandon and his Lucky Dog team join a local parade to raise awareness for animal rescue, some of his former students show up to support the cause.

26.title: Tank!
26.plot: Brandon trains a Tank, a black Lab, to alert a diabetic Navy vet when his blood sugar levels are low.

1.title: Wednesday
1.plot: Before a young Doberman Pinscher can become the best friend of a little boy with Autism, Brandon must make sure that the dog has the right temperament and training to help bring the boy out of his shell and assist him through life.

2.title: Cersei
2.plot: A young Husky mix could be the perfect match for a couple that plans to have kids. But, before Brandon hands over the reigns, he'll need to make sure that this very active dog has the right temperament for a family.

3.title: Mitzi
3.plot: A rescued Maltipoo puppy could be the perfect dog to help children during therapy. But, before she can take on this new role, she'll need to leave behind a bad jumping habit and arm herself with a new bag of tricks.

4.title: Milo
4.plot: Brandon turns to hand signals to train a deaf dog for a busy hotel executive. But, before he'll "sign-off" on the adoption, he must be completely confident that Milo's manners and temperament will result in more than just an overnight stay.

5.title: Lucy
5.plot: If Brandon can earn the trust of a fearful Chihuahua mix named Lucy, the dog could become the perfect companion for a partially paralyzed adrenaline junkie who's trying to get back on her feet.

6.title: Yogi
6.plot: Brandon helps Yogi, a chocolate Lab mix with anxiety.

7.title: Polly
7.plot: Polly, a timid German Shepherd mix, gets Brandon's help to be adopted by a couple with seven- and nine-year-old daughters.

8.title: Estella
8.plot: Brandon trains 5-year-old mystery mutt Estella to join a family with two 7-year-old boys, Max and Finn, and one dog, Pluto (see episode 2.5), a Tibetan terrier.

9.title: Ali
9.plot: Ali, a 10-month-old boxer, is trained for adoption by a father and his 14-year-old son, first-time dog owners who love the water.

12.title: Jax
12.plot: Brandon rescues Jax, a two-year old black shepherd-collie mix with hip dysplasia. After surgery to correct the condition, Brandon rehabilitates Jax so he can join the rescued animals at a farm owned by Brandon's friend.

18.title: Bella
18.plot: Brandon trains Bella, 1-1/2-year-old German short-hair pointer mix, abandoned by her family, to be adopted by a Palm Springs, California couple, Bob and Viv, who lost both their dogs to different illnesses on the same day.

19.title: Bobo
19.plot: Bobo, a spaniel mix, must have cataract surgery before he can be trained to be a companion dog for Vivian and her special-needs son Frankie.

20.title: Sparky
20.plot: After a spaniel mix that has been living on the streets is found, it must be tested to see if it can get along with other animals before being adopted.

23.title: Molly
23.plot: Mary Moore, a single mom, needs a therapy dog to help her 16-year-old autistic son Jack with his anxiety. Brandon trains a six-month-old Chihuahua mix for the job. Kris helps the family with their yard.

imdb.plot outline: Animal trainer Brandon McMillan's mission is to rescue difficult-to-love and untrained dogs that find themselves at the neighborhood animal shelter, his home away from home. At McMillan's training facility, Lucky Dog Ranch, he tackles the involved task of transforming dogs with behavioral issues into model pets. Each episode showcases the success story of a rehabilitated dog and the family that takes it home.
imdb.title: Lucky Dog
plot: Brandon trains dogs to the point where they can find forever homes.::szlennemann
